review_blob: Very nice Pilsner.  Crisp and clean with a very nice hop character that leaves you wanting another taste.
Very nice surprise.  More like a cream ale than anything else.  Smooth and sessionable.  Quite pleasant.
Not one of the better Clown Shoes beers - missing much interest.  The aroma was inviting, but very thin and leaves me not happy
This is my kind of IPA, the English type.  I like the malt flavors and hop flavors balanced and in harmony.  Might be the best one I have ever tried.
This is an awesome beer.  Great flavors of burnt fruits and malty tones.  Finish is warm and simply amazing.  I love this beer.
This beer is a treat.  Crisp and clean, but full of terrific malt tones and gentle bitterness.  Go out of your way to get this great beer.

Widmers first beer and best.  This should be their flagship, not the Hefe.  Wonderfully balanced beer with a wonderful matl backbone and hint of hoppy bitterness to dry the finish.  Wish it was available year-round.
Best IPA anywhere.  This has it all, wonderful bitterness, nice malt balance and terrific hoppy aroma.  No other IPA compares.
Ambers are not my usual style, but this is exceptional.  The flavor profile is well balanced and finishes with a hint of dryness.  Not too sweet, just right.

Finest strong scotch ale I have ever had the pleasure to enjoy.  Excellent aroma, wonderful smooth and lighly sweet initial tastes that are malt forward.  Finish is a combination of light sweet lingering and a hint of dry bitterness. Awesome!
